Degree of Similarity - 2
The overall pattern is similar and there are two features which appear in common above core but as you work out all remaining features are not in sequence and agreement. In the area on the mark of no activity (namely upper RHS), there are several features visible in the same area on the print. There are a good cluster of features below the core in the mark which were the main starting point for my comparison and looking at the same area on the print, they are clearly different. As I worked around the print, again the features present in one were not visible on the other.
Degree of Support - 1
I am of the opinion that these two impressions originated from a different source. I have observed almost no similarity between the two impressions.
